04/11/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Railway workers announced on Monday (November 3rd) they would stage a six-hour warning strike Friday to protest "poor" management decisions regarding the state railway company Caile Ferate Romane's (CFR) infrastructure. An estimated 7,000 people will participate in the strike. Unions representing teachers, public servants and medical workers are also planning massive protests for November, ahead of general elections on November 30th. (Evenimentul Zilei, Gardianl, Ziarul Nacional, Nine O'Clock - 04/11/08; Mediafax, Ziare, Hotnews, Realitatea TV - 03/11/08)
